author: wn.com
title: Budget
text: The 277-151 roll call Wednesday by which the House agreed to a short-term spending bill that will keep the government operating through Dec. 11, sending the bill to President Barack Obama. A "yes" vote is a vote to pass the bill. Voting yes were 186 Democrats and 91 Republicans. Voting no were 0 Democrats and 151 Republicans. X denotes those not voting. ALABAMA Democrats — Sewell, Y. Republicans — Aderholt, N; Brooks, N; Byrne, N; Palmer, N; Roby, N; Rogers, N. ALASKA Republicans — Young, Y. ARIZONA Democrats — Gallego, Y; Grijalva, Y; Kirkpatrick, Y; Sinema, Y. Republicans — Franks, N; Gosar, N; McSally, Y; Salmon, N; Schweikert, N. ARKANSAS Republicans — Crawford, N; Hill, N; Westerman, N; Womack, Y. ...
